                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At the request of President Truman, his Special Assistant, W. Averell Harriman,
                    made a trip to the Far East in early August. He held discussions with General
                    MacArthur in Tokyo on August 6 and 8, and with Ambassador Muccio in Korea on
                    August 7. Mr. Harriman’s notes on his conversations in Tokyo are printed under
                    date of August 8, <ref target="#pg_542">page 542</ref>; concerning his talk with
                    Ambassador Muccio on August 7, see <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
